{
  "stem": "10835.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In fact, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sometime-- at one time, as a matter of fact, she sent three girls to concentration camp in Auschwitz as a reprisal for being a little too chummy with the-- with the civilian people.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were nice to her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She was-- some people are just nice, you know, in every nationality, and this woman, at first, she-- this girl in particular, she was a daughter whose parents were old.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And at the time when we were first gathered at the river, when they first took us out of the house-- 1942, May 12-- her parents were immediately sent to Auschwitz and exterminated.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she was-- she was an only child.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She was very bitter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Very-- we were all bitter, of course, but she knew for a fact that her parents were exterminated.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We-- since we knew later that our parents went home, we were still hoping.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was going on for about maybe a year.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, they gave us paper.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- yes, they gave us paper.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for that year, things were going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We worked, we came home, we did our thing, we went to sleep, and we went to work the next day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we start-- yeah, my father still wrote cards to us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he didn't let on about all the things that happened.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then mail stopped, I think, close to, like, the end of 1942, beginning of '43.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The mail stopped coming.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So then they brought in another transport of people, and then we found out that the town of Modrzejow was converted into a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the two younger children remained there-- the brother and the sister remained in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
